    dc:creator "Roberto, Igor Joventino; Loebmann, Daniel; Lyra, Mariana L.; Ávila, Robson Waldemar" ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Pristimantis Jiménez de la Espada, 1870 (Anura: Strabomantidae) from the “ Brejos de Altitude ” in Northeast Brazil" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6224840>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6224846>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6224850>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6224856> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6224840>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Holotype of Pristimantis relictus sp. nov. (URCA-H 13344): Above—dorsal and ventral views; Below—head in lateral view; right hand and right foot in ventral view. Scale bars = 10mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6224840/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6224846>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Advertisement call of Pristimantis relictus sp. nov: A—individual, MNRJ 55582, recorded on the Serra da Aratanha mountain range, municipality of Pacatuba, state of Ceará, Brazil, on December 26, 2006 by Igor J. Roberto, showing one call composed of two notes, each with two distinct pulses. B–unvouchered individual from the Serra de Baturité mountain range, municipality of Pacoti, state of Ceará, recorded on February 11, 2007, by Igor J. Roberto, showing a call composed of eight pulsed notes. Spectrogram (above) and oscillogram (below)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6224846/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6224850>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Adult specimens of Pristimantis relictus sp. nov. in life: A—Adult male, B–D adult female, municipality of Ubajara; E–F adult female municipality of Guaramiranga, G—amplectant pair, municipality of Pacatuba; H–I—adult calling males, municipality of Guaramiranga, state of Ceará, Brazil." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6224850/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6224856>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Geographic distribution map of Pristimantis relictus: yellow triangle, type locality in the Ubajara National Park, Serra da Ibiapaba mountain range; green circles, localities of paratypes: 1-municipality of Tianguá, 2-Serra da Ubatuba mountain range, municipality of Granja, 3-Serra da Meruoca mountain range, 4-municipality of Ipu, 5-Serra da Uruburetama mountain range, 6-Serra de Baturité mountain range, 7-Serra de Maranguape mountain range, 8-Serra da Aratanha mountain range." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6224856/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

